==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Logical
<hw>Log"ic*al</hw> <pr>(l⟦ocr⟧j"⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>logique</ets>, L. <ets>logicus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>logiko`s</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to logic;
used in logic; <as>as, <ex>logical</ex> subtilties</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>According to the rules of logic; <as>as, a
<ex>logical</ex> argument or inference; the reasoning is
<ex>logical</ex>; a <ex>logical</ex> argument; a <ex>logical</ex>
impossibility.</as></def> <rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Skilled in logic; versed in the art of thinking and
reasoning; <as>as, he is a <ex>logical</ex> thinker</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Logicality</ent>⟦br⟧
